## Scenario 7 — NPDES Permit Exceedance at a Direct-Discharge Outfall
##
## Module D (CWA). Direct-discharge outfall under an NPDES individual
## permit. Effluent-limit exceedance drives 24-hour noncompliance
## reporting (40 CFR 122.41(l)(6)) with 5-day written follow-up and
## monthly DMR (40 CFR 122.41(l)(7)). EPA-only routing: no OSHA unless
## a worker exposure pathway exists during sampling/response.
##
## Key distinction from Scenario 8: NPDES numeric limits are
## enforceable violations, not benchmark exceedances.
##
## Baseline triples extracted from ehs-ontology-v3.2.ttl (line 1303).

PREFIX ehs: <http://example.org/ehs-ontology#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

ASK {
    ehs:Scenario_NPDESPermitExceedance rdf:type ehs:ContextualComplianceActivation ;
        ehs:triggeredByType       ehs:ChemicalHazard ;
        ehs:hasActionContext      ehs:ProcessingAction ;
        ehs:hasContextCondition   ehs:WaterwayProximity ,
                                  ehs:FullRelease ;
        ehs:activatesFramework    ehs:EPA_Framework .
}
